Wash and dry all produce. Drain the @artichokes{1%jar}. Halve the artichokes lengthwise and pat dry between two layers of #paper towel{}. Thinly slice the @green olives{1%ounce}. Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Pick the @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves of the stems. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and dice the @russet potato{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

Heat a ¼-inch layer of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the potatoes and fry ~{8-10%minutes}, turning to brown on all sides, until golden brown and crispy. Remove from the olive oil and reserve on a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the artichokes to the same pan. Fry ~{5-6%minutes} over medium-high heat, turning to cook on all sides, until golden brown and crispy. Remove from the olive oil and reserve on a paper-towel-lined plate. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @mayonnaise{1%jar}, @white wine vinegar{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of garlic (to taste) and as much @chipotle powder{1%tsp} as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

  Add @arugula{2%ounce}, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}(halved), @almonds{1%ounce}(sliced), olives, @feta cheese{1/4%cup}, potatoes, and artichokes.

Drizzle the patatas bravas salad with spicy aioli, garnish with parsley leaves, and enjoy!